Small businesses that don’t qualify for bank loans have many options available to them, however often times these options come with conditions that make it difficult for small businesses to We believe that relationships are the key to success and as such, hold Trust, Integrity, and Respect, as part of our core At Aequum, we strive to provide financing that is right, fair, and equitable to all OUR STORY Aequum is a company started by five career lending executives and entrepreneurs with over years of collective We are a commercial lending platform for companies looking to find financing between $1MM and $10MM who are not otherwise eligible for traditional bank Aequum’s platform allows for efficient underwriting, funding, servicing, and portfolio management to ensure low overhead costs that can be passed on to our We are taking a consultative lending approach and bringing Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) policies to improve our borrower’s operations and ultimately provide a path to traditional bank Using this strategy, we will create an ecosystem where each stakeholder in the process (the borrowers, bank partners, investors, and sponsorship) are incentivized to optimize ESG philosophies, in particular governance, at the borrowers OUR MISSION To level the commercial finance competitive landscape by providing lower middle market borrowers, that have the potential and willingness to have a meaningful environmental, social, or corporate governance impact, access to structured capital and top tier back office service solutions allowing them to compete on a more competitive scale, and in time, gain access to more traditional OUR VISION To create a business lending and partnering ecosystem that combines specialty finance expertise and best practices with proprietary technologies, process engineering and methodologies resulting in accelerated, dynamic and better business WHAT IS ESG ESG stands for Environmental, Social and Governance, and refers to three central factors in measuring the long term sustainability of a Environmental criteria examine how a business contributes to and performs on environmental challenges (e.g. waste, pollution, emissions, climate change, and treatment of animals). Social criteria look at how the company treats people (e.g. diversity and equal opportunities, work environment, health and safety, and community). Governance criteria examine how a company is governed (e.g. accurate and transparent accounting, and bribery, governing structure, checks and balances, and board diversity and structure). HOW DO WE COMBINE ESG AND COMMERCIAL LENDING? Aequum Capital Founder, LLC (Aequum) looks at companies from ESG perspectives to evaluate their standing relative to peers through a proprietary scoring Aequum strongly believes that companies that improve their ESG score, specifically as it relates to Governance can improve performance and its ability to repay Just as with other credit metrics, Aequum expects improving ESG profiles to lead to a lower cost of capital and have built this belief into our underwriting practices to reward our borrowers for impro

treatments for ALS and other neurodegenerative diseases, today announced its corporate launch, the expansion of its executive team and the creation of its Scientific Advisory Neuvivo’s lead candidate, caused by this devastating Neuvivo is bringing together a powerhouse team to carry forward its mission, including seasoned industry executives, clinicians, and pioneer scientists with extensive backgrounds in ALS research and multiple product approval “Our Scientific Advisory Board has some of the world’s leading ALS scientists and clinicians who will help us achieve our goals, and we are excited to add executives to our management team who have extensive experience in achieving approvals for new drugs,” said Neuvivo founder and CEO, Ari Azhir, “We are pleased to be working with the FDA and are doing all in our power to be responsive to the needs of ALS patients and patient advocates to provide a safer and significantly more effective ALS ” “NP001 is a first in class NCE and an entirely new approach to treating ALS,” said and Chief Scientific Officer, Michael McGrath, MD, PhD, Emeritus Professor of Medicine at “We know now that chronic inflammation is a key factor in the loss of motor neuron function in NP001’s mechanism of action targets macrophages to reduce inflammation and restore immune system ” Current research points to compromised macrophage function as a critical factor in many CNS diseases including Parkinson’s and Alzheimer’s, suggesting that small molecule NP001 could potentially be used as a treatment for other Founding Executive Team Ari Azhir, experienced the amount of care required for mechanically ventilated For her company, Swiftsure Innovation, above all, their mission is to support patients by developing products that will help prevent To do this, Swiftsure created a novel device that aims to revolutionize oral care for ventilated Their new solution focuses on improving patient outcomes, protecting frontline workers and benefiting Swiftsure is the latest company to join Emergence, Atlantic Canada’s bioscience business incubator dedicated to assisting and companies in efficiently bringing their products and services to “With the assistance of Emergence, we are doing market research to establish current perceptions of oral care to receive direct input from end users about our Establishing feedback from ICU physicians, Registered Nurses, and Respiratory Therapists is an essential part of driving a design that will best serve patients and improve patient outcomes,” said Deanne McCarthy, CEO and Founder, Swiftsure “Being supported by Emergence has helped Swiftsure progress in a very meaningful It is great to have such awesome support here in Atlantic Canada!” The challenge with ventilators While mechanical ventilation provides treatment for critically ill patients, the problem is that the endotracheal tube that connects the ventilator to the patient’s lungs provides a direct route for germs to enter the This can result in pneumonia, the most fatal and costly of The problem associated with ventilators has also intensified as a result of the Swiftsure is developing a device that will facilitate the moisturization and cleansing of the mouth and nose of patients on ventilators by flushing them with Their product will also improve the seal for further germ They are currently in the design development phase, working with partners at the National Research Council and Dalhousie In , they were the winner of the annual BioInnovation Challenge pitch competition at BioPort As a client of Emergence, Swiftsure will have access to business incubation services including mentorship and advisory services, team mentorship program as well as access to networks and For more information on He and his colleagues put together, literally from scratch, a massive scientific research project involving universities, inventing new techniques for extracting information from the longest ice cores ever from the planet’s harshest His book — equally a scientific explanation of startling new discoveries, an account of how researchers actually work, and a depiction of real life scientific adventure — arrestingly depicts the contemporary world of climate change The Ice Chronicles tells the story behind GISP2, and its product ,000 years of climate These amazing frozen records document major environmental events such as volcanoes and forest They also reveal the dramatic influence that humans have had on the chemistry of the atmosphere and climate change through major additions of greenhouse gases, acid rain, and stratospheric ozone Perhaps the most startling new information gleaned from these records is the knowledge that natural climate is far from stable quite the opposite — major, fast changes in climate are found throughout the It now appears that Earth’s climate changes dramatically every few thousand years, often within the span of a Data gathered through ice core analysis challenge traditional assumptions of how climate Further, the authors show that climate conditions over the past several thousand years, which we take for granted as normal, may in fact be significantly different from that in the previous ,000 New data suggest

He and his colleagues put together, literally from scratch, a massive scientific research project involving universities, inventing new techniques for extracting information from the longest ice cores ever from the planet’s harshest His book — equally a scientific explanation of startling new discoveries, an account of how researchers actually work, and a depiction of real life scientific adventure — arrestingly depicts the contemporary world of climate change The Ice Chronicles tells the story behind GISP2, and its product ,000 years of climate These amazing frozen records document major environmental events such as volcanoes and forest They also reveal the dramatic influence that humans have had on the chemistry of the atmosphere and climate change through major additions of greenhouse gases, acid rain, and stratospheric ozone Perhaps the most startling new information gleaned from these records is the knowledge that natural climate is far from stable quite the opposite — major, fast changes in climate are found throughout the It now appears that Earth’s climate changes dramatically every few thousand years, often within the span of a Data gathered through ice core analysis challenge traditional assumptions of how climate Further, the authors show that climate conditions over the past several thousand years, which we take for granted as normal, may in fact be significantly different from that in the previous ,000 New data suggest

SPRX Home About Pricing FAQ Blog SPRX Tips Log in Log in Tip #40 â Evaluate your provider Evaluate your R&D credit provider, they may not be the expert you expect them to Your R&D credit is a big It may be the most beneficial, most time consuming, most contentious, and most audited item on your tax Shouldnât you have the best team possible working on it? â Not all R&D credit experts are Donât be fooled by the many folks marketing themselves and posing as tax â SPRX R&D Credit Tip â Evaluate your R&D credit provider, they may not be the expert you expect them to Trust but verify Trust but verify, a phrase made popular by Ronald Regan, is an English translation of a Russian proverb â âDoveryai, no proveryaiâ. It literally means a responsible person always verifies before doing business with â With social media today, why would you not take a moment to evaluate your R&D credit You can quickly check professional backgrounds on Link up with your R&D credit provider and quickly check the following: â Who is doing the work? Do they know accounting? Are they a CPA or a tax attorney? What is their R&D credit experience? Will they be there tomorrow? â Evaluate your R&D credit provider and verify they have the experience you Who is doing the work? Tax consultants like to use bait and switch An experienced partner comes out to meet with you and explain their Then as soon as you sign the contract a separate implementation team comes out to run the You never benefit from the expertise you thought you were â The other day a tax director shared a story Iâve heard several She had worked with an R&D partner and manager for a few She was happy with the results they As the next year R&D study began, she noticed there was a new staff person assigned to her She didnât think much of it because after all she had the same partner and manager As the project started things started to fall She soon discovered that it had been the staff person who was doing all the great The partner and manager were hiding behind the excellent performance of the â Check staff They are the ones who will be making your tax Do they know accounting? Firms have hired people with all types of backgrounds and marketed them as R&D credit There are people with degrees in mathematics, history, comparative literature, art history, sociology, health studies, and psychology holding themselves out as tax experts and performing R&D â These persons may know a few tax rules and spreadsheet functions, but they are missing the professional and analytical skills expected from You should expect your tax consultant to have been trained in professional skepticism and to not simply accept information at face value but to verify the information through You should expect them to know how to vouch, trace, organize, think critically, and interpret â Basic accounting skills are fundamental to a successful tax Are they a CPA or tax attorney? Many senior professionals working as R&D credit experts are not CPAs or tax You may correctly ask, âhow can that be?â â Accounting firms have had to change partnership admission requirements to accommodate R&D credit professionals who drive revenue but who cannot pass the CPA or bar â Whoâs making your tax decisions? Are you comfortable taking tax advice from a business analyst, material control specialist, editor, or civil engineer? What is their R&D credit experience? The R&D credit is a provision in the tax There is a complex regulatory and judicial history behind the R&D Understanding this history is essential to maximizing and defending your R&D Â â Yet many of todayâs R&D credit âexpertsâ are ignorant of this They have not had experience reading, studying, and applying the various regulations and court Lack of experience can lead to terrible â Imagine you are in a meeting with an IRS The agent offers an outlandish interpretation of a tax You look to your CPA for a The CPA is shell shocked, confused, and unable to At best the CPA replies with, âI will need to check that and get back with youâ . majority (95%) is located in regions of the These areas are highly enriched in DNA regulatory elements such as gene enhancers that regulate in which cells and under what conditions genes are turned on and A major challenge in interpreting the function of these DNA regulatory elements and variants is that they can be located really far away (up to millions of base pairs) from the genes they regulate on the linear genomic However, the two meters of DNA in each of our cell nuclei is not present in the linear form – it is folded in a manner that differs from cell type to cell type, and it is through this folding of the genome that enhancers come into close proximity to the specific genes they control to regulate their Enhanc3D Genomics’ disruptive technology profiles this genome folding at high resolution for all genes and their enhancers simultaneously, and thus links gene enhancers and genetic variants to their target genes to unlock their potential for therapeutic About Team Contact
